Package: disco
Type: Package
Title: Density-Based Internal Score for Clustering Outcomes
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Amin", "Entezari", email = "amin_entezari@outlook.com", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Anna", "Beer", role = "aut", comment = "Original Python implementation"),
    person("Lena", "Krieger", role = "aut", comment = "Original Python implementation"),
    person("Pascal", "Weber", role = "aut", comment = "Original Python implementation"))
Description: Implementation of DISCO (Density-based Internal Score for Clustering 
    Outcomes), a cluster validity index for evaluating density-based clustering results. 
    DISCO is the first CVI that explicitly evaluates the quality of noise labels in 
    addition to cluster quality. It assesses compactness and separation using 
    density-connectivity distance while providing interpretable, bounded scores.
